               <head>Anglo-Russian relations</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85085222 http://lccn.loc.gov/n80001203 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2009117611 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85064915 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2007100239" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4073-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Untitled and anonymous (secret?) report on Anglo-Russian political and military relations, detailing British measures to confront Russian Imperial expansion in the 1820s-30s, possibly prepared for or by officials of the Bengal Presidency</p>
                        <p>Mentions the attitudes and involvement of rulers in Iran, Afghanistan, Ottoman Turkey, Africa (Zangī), and China, and covering subjects like food, provisioning, military movements, itineraries, and the burning of books</p>
                        <p>The narrative is continuous, lacking systematic dating, rubrics, preface or introduction. Versified conclusion (ff. 141v-148r)</p>
                        <p>Colophon (f. 148) in 2 parts: 1) chronogrammatic verse stating the manuscript was written at the request of Arjun Singh in 1893; 2) prose subscription in Urdu: <q>vāẓiḥ ho kih yih kitāb aṣal 19 Bisākh-i sanah 1893 Bikramī men̲ tayyār hūʾī</q>. William Irvine has converted the Bikrami date to 1836 CE.
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="urd" xml:lang="per">Persian and Urdu</textLang>
                     <note>Copied from an original =-=-=-=-</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
